trend_summary: Predominantly rural land persisted, with only modest town-edge infill and roadside ribbon growth. Some cropland parcels reverted to woodland, darkening western and central blocks, while crop rotation changed field tones yearly. A clearer east-west roadway and a few new ponds mark limited infrastructure and drainage upgrades over time.
notable_changes: Slow outward growth of the southern settlement and scattered roadside houses
Emergence of a more continuous east-west connector road
Noticeable reforestation of several former fields in the western half
Shifting crop patterns altering field coloration and extent
Creation of small water bodies or retention ponds in the northeast quadrant
